[b]Coteries of New York[/b] is a visual novel inspired by [b]New York by Night[/b]. Despite the fact that outcomes of your choices have very minor variations, the story is solid, the artwork is beautiful (albeit not to my taste), the characters are memorable and fleshed out, and the overall presentation is immersive.

As a game [b]CoNY[/b] is nothing great, but as a novel it's pretty good. I have only minor complaints about it:

[list]
[*] Incomplete understanding of anatomy (not possible to sink fangs into the aorta through skin; not possible to drink from aorta without losing enough blood to kill the victim);
[*] Inconsistencies between the text and artwork (e.g., T-shirt vs dress);
[*] Inconsistencies between the text and choices (e.g., reference to a "snack" in a situation where the PC decided not to feed);
[*] The fledgling has knowledge of the vampire lore that no one shared with him (e.g., connection between phones and SI, understanding of the difference between the Camarilla and non-Camarilla clans;
[*] Recycled locations (same location artwork for different locations);
[*] Investigation scenes are very primitive;
[*] The story ends on a cliffhanger.
[/list]

I recommend this game to all fans of [i]Dark World[/i] universe and, simply, to everyone who likes a good vampire story. I think it's a bit overpriced for a visual novel and compared to other games that offer more content, so I'd recommend to wait for sales.

[b]My overall rating[/b]: [u]7/10[/u]

